This is the documentation for AMEEconnect, written in docbook 4.4.

Requirements
------------

Assuming OSX:

  docbook (install via homebrew)
  xsltproc
  fop (PDF only)
  Ruby 1.9.2 (and bundler) for automated builds and sample generation

Automated Build
---------------

From the root directory, run:
* bundle
* guard

This should set up automatic building of the HTML documentation. A config.ru file is included
so you can view it with pow.cx if you want to.

Manual Build
------------

To build, go into the src directory and run: ../tools/book-dist.py 

options:
  --html: HTML single page
  --html-chunk: HTML multi page
  --pdf: PDF